seal     : Everything that exchanges with the world does it through a surface: the cell through its membrane, the body through its skin, the program through its interface, two people through the words between them. The interface is the thinnest part of any system and the most important — where inside meets outside, where two worlds touch without becoming one. To control the interface is to control the exchange.
